ds that can explain the impact of data augmentation on text data, ensuring that the transformations are meaningful and do not introduce errors.\n\n**Collaborative Brainstorming:**\n- The team is expected to brainstorm potential research ideas that address the continuity problem in text data augmentation and the need for explainable methods.\n- The focus should be on developing methodologies that can provide insights into how data augmentation techniques affect text data and the derived classifiers.\n\n**Formulating a New Research Idea:**\n- The team is tasked with developing a new research proposal in the format of the '5q' to address the identified problem.\n- The proposal should clearly outline the problem, its importance, the challenges involved, the reasons it hasn't been solved before, and the key components of the proposed approach.\n\n### Proposed '5q' Research Idea\n\n**[Question 1] - What is the problem?**\nWhat are the specific mechanisms and methods that can be developed to ensure continuity and explainability in text data augmentation?\n\n**[Question 2] - Why is it interesting and important?**\nAddressing the continuity and explainability issues in text data augmentation is crucial for improving the reliability and interpretability of machine learning models. Solving this problem will enhance the quality of training data, leading to better-performing classifiers and more trustworthy AI systems. This research will contribute to the broader field of machine learning by providing a deeper understanding of how data augmentation techniques affect text data.\n\n**[Question 3] - Why is it hard?**\nThe challenge lies in developing methods that can accurately explain the impact of data augmentation on text data while ensuring that the transformations maintain the continuity and meaning of the text. Naive approaches may fail to capture the nuances of text data, leading to unintended changes in class information or meaning. Technical, theoretical, and practical obs